collections.name: PXL DEX
collections.description:
PXL DEX is a series of fully on-chain real time animations, where each pixel is a token in itself. PXL DEX is the first artwork within the PXL ecosystem, an ongoing work series to experiment with pixels as utility tokens. The collection consists of 256 NFTs that are deployed via a custom Smart Contract on the Ethereum Mainnet.

The NFTs can be minted for 0.5 ETH plus 0.000001 ETH per pixel. Each pixel is actually a PXL token and will initially be owned by the PXL DEX Smart Contract to be assigned to the minted NFT. PXL tokens can be withdrawn and deposited by the owner. The minter is allowed to mint up to 500.000 PXL tokens along with the NFT. Each Deck has an additional allowance of 500.000 PXL to be minted any time later. The allowance is bound to the NFT and will transfer along with the NFT ownership.

A single Deck can hold all available PXL tokens, there is no limit on the Smart Contract level. The only limitation is the GPU of the computer that displays the Deck.

collections.name: Guardian Sigils
collections.description:
Guardian Sigils are a 100% onchain, dynamic, animated, and interactive generative art collection, with all traits and artwork code generated onchain by a single smart contract. The contract generates image assets and HTML that any modern browser can use to render the art – but the Guardian Sigil art only renders if the account holding the NFT is a $PLEDGE Guardian (has an active pledge of 1M tokens). Learn more at https://www.thepledge.meme/

If the token is held by an account that is not a $PLEDGE Guardian, then the background will render but not a sigil. Trading the token with a Guardian or becoming one will reveal the Guardian Sigil!

Tokens can have different traits and rarities that never change, but every account’s sigil will be constant across all tokens it owns. Guardian Sigil tokens are dynamic, and they will always update themselves to draw their owner’s sigil (if they’re a Guardian).

collections.name: I ❤️ LA
collections.description:
In response to the devastating wildfires that have impacted individuals and families across Los Angeles, mmERCH has collaborated with seven acclaimed digital artists to launch the ‘I ❤️ LA’ NFT collection in an effort to raise vital funds for those most impacted by this ongoing tragedy. mmERCH, along with all participating artists, will donate 100% of proceeds raised from the sale to Baby2Baby, a nonprofit organization that provides essential supplies to children and families in crisis.

The project brings together the talents of seven renowned digital artists, including: Larva Labs (Matt Hall and John Watkinson), Grant Yun, Gremplin, Nice Aunties, Chikai, ClownVamp, and Goyong.

collections.name: Lonely Chair
collections.description:
Lonely Chair explores identity in the digital age. In a world where NFTs and virtual spaces redefine human presence, identity exists as data, imagery, and blockchain entries. 
This shift challenges traditional notions of individuality and raises questions about what it means to exist in an increasingly virtual reality. 
Lonely Chair examines how we navigate the paradox of being simultaneously visible and intangible. The collection invites viewers to consider the implications of a new type of human presence—one that transcends the physical and exists in the digital realm.
Collectors receive printed editions of their NFTs, with Oblivion available as an edition of 9 and Bloom offered as a unique 1/1 artwork.

collections.description: In a world where every pixel tells a story, this image stands out as a compelling narrative of resilience and perspective. The essence of measure emerges from the harmonious interplay of skilfulness and precision. It is through the adept application of one's craft and the meticulous attention to detail that true accuracy is attained. In this confluence, we find a reflection of a deeper truth: that mastery and careful discernment are the foundation upon which reliable and meaningful measurements are built. Thus, the rule of measure is not merely a technical guideline but a philosophical testament to the pursuit of excellence and the quest for understanding.
